ia |first2=L. |title=Coronavirus Disease 2019 (COVID-19): Role of Chest CT in Diagnosis and Management |journal=American Journal of Roentgenology |pages=1\u20137 |date=March 2020 |pmid=32130038 |doi=10.2214/AJR.20.22954}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"web\">{{cite web |url=https://publichealthmatters.blog.gov.uk/2020/02/13/expert-interview-what-is-contact-tracing/ |title=Expert interview: What is contact tracing? |work=Blog: Public Health Matters |publisher=[[Public Health England]], Government of the United Kingdom |access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"WHO masks\">{{cite web |url=https://www.who.int/emergencies/diseases/novel-coronavirus-2019/advice-for-public/when-and-how-to-use-masks |title=Coronavirus disease (COVID-19) advice for the public: When and how to use masks |work=[[World Health Organization]] |access-date=9 March 2020 |url-status=live |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200307013848/https://www.who.int/emergencies/diseases/novel-coronavirus-2019/advice-for-public/when-and-how-to-use-masks |archive-date=7 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"nhc_masks\">{{cite web |url=http://en.nhc.gov.cn/2020-02/07/c_76337.htm |title=For different groups of people: how to choose masks |work=NHC.gov.cn |publisher=National Health Commission of the People's Republic of China |date=7 February 2020 |access-date=22 March 2020 |archive-url= |archive-date= |quote=\"Disposable medical masks: Recommended for: \u00b7 People in crowded places \u00b7 Indoor working environment with a relatively dense population \u00b7 People going to medical institutions \u00b7 Children in kindergarten and students at school gathering to study and do other activities\"}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"march18.radio.cz\">{{cite news |url=https://www.radio.cz/en/section/news/government-bans-going-out-without-covered-mouth-and-nose |title=Government bans going out without covered mouth and nose |date=18 March 2020 |work=radio.cz|access-date=18 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Lancet2020Flatten\">{