{"title_page": "List of American Dad! episodes", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=October 2019}}\n{{DISPLAYTITLE:List of ''American Dad!'' episodes}}\n[[File:American dad logo.svg|right|250px]]\n''[[American Dad!]]'' is an American [[adult animation|adult]] [[animated sitcom]] created by [[Seth MacFarlane]], [[Mike Barker (producer)|Mike Barker]], and [[Matt Weitzman]] that debuted on February 6, 2005 for the [[Fox Broadcasting Company]]. Set in the fictional town of Langley Falls, Virginia, the series centers on the eccentric Smith family. The Smith family consists of title character [[Stan Smith (American Dad!)|Stan]], [[Francine Smith|Francine]], [[Hayley Smith (American Dad!)|Hayley]], [[Steve Smith (American Dad!)|Steve]], [[Roger (American Dad!)|Roger]] (an [[Extraterrestrial life|alien]] whom Stan has rescued from government capture and harbors in the family's attic), [[List of American Dad! characters#Jeff Smith (formerly Fischer)|Jeff Fischer]] (Hayley's boyfriend), and [[Klaus Heissler|Klaus]] (the family's pet who is really an [[East Germany|East German]] man trapped by the CIA in a fish's body).\n\nAs of January 2020, ''American Dad!'' has broadcast 276 episodes, currently airing the sixteenth season. The series' [[American Dad! (season 11)|11th season]] was its final season to air on Fox.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.latintimes.com/articles/8802/20130929/american-dad-season-9-premiere-when-where-watch-tv-online.htm#.UklD3f4o7X4 |title='American Dad' Season 10 Premiere: When And Where To Watch 'Steve And Snot\u2019s Test Tube-Tube Adventure' On TV and Online [VIDEO&#93; : Entertainment |publisher=Latin Times |date= |accessdate=September 30, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/seth-macfarlane-family-guy-american-dad-cleveland-show-bobs-burgers-323080 |title=Seth MacFarlane's 'Family Guy,' 'American Dad' Renewed Through 2013\u201314 |publisher=Hollywoodreporter.com |date=October 5, 2012 |accessdate=April 4, 2013}}</ref> The show moved to the cable network [[TBS (U.S. TV channel)|TBS]] beginning with the 12th season.  \n\nOn January 11, 2018, TBS renewed the series for a 16th and 17th season of 22 episodes each, bringing the total number of episodes to 300.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2018/tv/news/american-dad-renewed-final-space-tbs-1202661133/|title=TBS Renews \u2018American Dad\u2019 for Two More Seasons, Sets Monday Night Animation Block|first1=Joe|last1=Otterson|first2=Joe|last2=Otterson|date=January 11, 2018}}</ref> The 16th season premiered on April 15, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/listings/20190325tbs01/|title=AMERICAN DAD on TBS |publisher=Thefutoncritic.com |date= |accessdate=April 5, 2019}}</ref>\n\n{{TOC right}}\n\n== Series overview ==\n<onlyinclude>{{Series overview\n\n| color1     = #68B1DE\n| link1      = <includeonly>List of American Dad! episodes</includeonly>#Season 1 (2005)\n| episodes1  = 7\n| start1     = {{Start date|2005|2|6}}\n| end1       = {{End date|2005|6|19}}\n| network1   = [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]]\n\n| color2     = #2E516C\n| link2      = <includeonly>List of American Dad! episodes</includeonly>#Season 2 (2005\u201306)\n| episodes2  = 16\n| start2     = {{Start date|2005|9|11}}\n| end2       = {{End date|2006|5|14}}\n\n| color3     = #A91B23\n| link3      = <includeonly>List of American Dad! episodes</includeonly>#Season 3 (2006\u201307)\n| episodes3  = 19\n| start3     = {{Start date|2006|9|10}}\n| end3       = {{End date|2007|5|20}}\n\n| color4     = #F68D22\n| link4      = <includeonly>List of American Dad! episodes</includeonly>#Season 4 (2007\u201308)\n| episodes4  = 16\n| start4     = {{Start date|2007|9|30}}\n| end4       = {{End date|2008|5|18}}\n\n| color5     = #A9BE61\n| link5      = <includeonly>List of American Dad! episodes</includeonly>#Season 5 (2008\u201309)\n| episodes5  = 20\n| start5     = {{Start date|2008|9|28}}\n| end5       = {{End d